Plot: In the third volume of The Lord of the Rings trilogy the good and evil forces join battle, and we see that the triumph of good is not absolute. The Third Age of Middle-earth ends, and the age of the dominion of Men begins.
Characters: Frodo Baggins, Meriadoc Brandybuck, Peregrin Took, Gandalf, Aragorn, Gimli, Bilbo Baggins, Saruman, Éowyn, Éomer, Elrond Half-elven, Arwen Undómiel, Galadriel, Faramir, Gollum, Legolas, Sam Gamgee
